        "source": "Bush_-_As_We_May_Think_(Life_Magazine_9-10-1945).pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Scientific research",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The growing body of research findings and conclusions produced by many workers, creating an information overload for individual investigators.",
        "context": "Bush notes that the mountain of research is becoming difficult to manage and remember.",
        "tags": [
          "science",
          "information overload"
        ],
